body:
All the examples, I have checked, appear to draw the correct graphics colors on an Android emulator. However, Visual Studio shows strange values on SKPaint Color property.

Sample code

```
    public static void TestPaintColor(SKCanvas canvas, int width, int height)
    {
        SKColor color = SKColors.Red;
        SKPaint paint = new SKPaint();
        paint.Color = color;

        if (!paint.Color.Equals(color))
        {
            System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("SKPaint.Color issue (" + paint.Color + " != " + color + ")");
        }
    }
```

VIsual Studio output:

[0:] SKPaint.Color issue (#a3c3f220 != #ffff0000)

Regards,
Olli Raisa
